10.11	Blairism	Blairism	In British politics, the term Blairism refers to the political ideology of former leader of the Labour Party and Prime Minister Tony Blair, who left both positions in 2007 to become Envoy of the Quartet on the Middle East. Proponents of Blairism are referred to as Blairites.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c0/TonyBlairArmagh1998.jpg/220px-TonyBlairArmagh1998.jpg
